"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641235","Department for Education","false","2016-11-25","<p>The Education Funding Agency published a report about Bright Tribe Trust on 9 November 2016. This report sets out the recommendations made by EFA in December 2015 and includes details of the Trust’s progress in implementing them. A copy of this report is now in the Library.</p>","Crewe and Nantwich","Edward Timpson",,"2016-11-25T13:12:39.803Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641235/answer","Biography information for Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641235/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641235/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-11-21","Bright Tribe Multi Academy Trust","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, if she will place a copy of the 2015 report on Bright Tribe Multi Academy Trust prepared by the Risk Analysis Division of the Education Funding Agency in the Library.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","53969"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641236","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2016-11-28","<p>Bass have been in serious decline due to fishing pressure and an earlier succession of winters with poor reproduction. The latest proposals for measures to apply at EU level in 2017 are due to be agreed at December Fisheries Council.</p><p> </p><p>I recognise the level of challenge the restrictions on bass catches in 2017, as proposed by the European Commission, would present for both recreational and commercial fishing sectors. We are considering the Commission’s proposals carefully, including the absence of any provision for sea bass caught in nets to be landed. We will be seeking to secure a balanced package of measures which builds on the progress to date to continue to bring bass catches down to a recommended level while the stock recovers. This is a UK Government priority, to secure sustainable fishing for bass in the long term</p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2016-11-28T12:16:44.417Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641236/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641236/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641236/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2016-11-21","White Fish: Fishing Catches","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what her policy is on a temporary ban on the commercial netting of sea bass.","false","Biography information for Danny Kinahan","South Antrim","Danny Kinahan","53937"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641237","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2016-11-25","<p>There are currently no plans to introduce a deposit return system. We will continue to review new evidence regarding such schemes.</p>","Suffolk Coastal","Dr Thérèse Coffey",,"2016-11-25T13:12:11.39Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641237/answer","Biography information for Dr Thérèse  Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641237/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641237/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2016-11-21","Beverage Containers: Recycling","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, if she will make it her policy to introduce the bottle deposit return system proposed by Surfers Against Sewage.","false","Biography information for Danny Kinahan","South Antrim","Danny Kinahan","53933"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641238","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2016-11-28","<p>Defra supports the efficient use of fertiliser, through agri-environment schemes that promote environmentally sensitive land management and also through capital investments into new, innovative technologies that optimise application.</p><p> </p><p>Overall, fertiliser use is declining across the UK as the annual report from the British Fertiliser Survey outlines.</p><p> </p><p>The application of total nitrogen has declined by 28% from 1983 to 2015 across Great Britain. For the same time period phosphate and potash have seen a decline of 55% and 44% respectively.</p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2016-11-28T16:07:40.54Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641238/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641238/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641238/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2016-11-21","Agriculture: Fertilisers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, pursuant to the Answer of 18 November 2016 to Question 53157, what steps she is taking to reduce the level of application of (a) nitrogen, (b) phosphate, (c) potash and (d) sulphur on UK farmland while maintaining levels of output; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","53991"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641239","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2016-11-25","<p>The UK’s Marine and Coastal Access Act 2009 (MCAA) includes a marine licensing regime, under Part 4, for most marine activities. The Act regulates dumping of waste at sea including navigational dredging and disposal under the Waste Framework Directive.</p><p> </p><p>The Prime Minister has announced a Repeal Bill to convert EU law into domestic British law, to provide certainty for consumers, workers and businesses by maintaining existing laws.</p><p> </p><p>As domestic legislation the MCAA will continue to be in place when the UK has left the EU. There is no current intention to change the regulatory framework in respect of the dumping of waste in the marine environment.</p><p> </p><p>In Scotland this is covered by the Marine (Scotland) Act 2010.</p>","Suffolk Coastal","Dr Thérèse Coffey",,"2016-11-25T13:08:40.627Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641239/answer","Biography information for Dr Thérèse  Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641239/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641239/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2016-11-21","Waste Disposal: Seas and Oceans","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what steps her Department plans to take to maintain protection for coastal towns from the sea dumping of waste after the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Neil Coyle","Bermondsey and Old Southwark","Neil Coyle","53931"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641240","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2016-11-24","<p>The first step towards developing the plan will be to publish soon the framework which will be open to all to contribute. We will use the feedback from this to help develop the full plan itself next year.</p>","Suffolk Coastal","Dr Thérèse Coffey",,"2016-11-24T11:45:26.817Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641240/answer","Biography information for Dr Thérèse  Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641240/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641240/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2016-11-21","Environment Protection: Public Consultation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what plans her Department has for members of the public to contribute to the consultation on its 25 year plan for the natural environment.","false","Biography information for Kerry McCarthy","Bristol East","Kerry McCarthy","53904"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641241","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2016-11-29","<p>The latest report (UK-VARSS 2015) was published on GOV.UK on the 17 November 2016. The report contains sales of antibiotics indicated for food-producing animals. As an agreed harmonised EU method is used to calculate these data it also includes horses.</p><p> </p><p>The report shows that sales reduced by 10% from 62mg/PCU in 2014 to 56mg/PCU in 2015, taking it to the lowest level in four years.</p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2016-11-29T17:14:04.957Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641241/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641241/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641241/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2016-11-21","Livestock: Antibiotics","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what estimate she has made of the level of antibiotic use in meat-producing animals in each of the last five years; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","54040"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641242","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2016-11-25","<p>Until exit negotiations are concluded, the UK remains a full member of the European Union (EU) and all the rights and obligations of EU membership remain in force.</p><p> </p><p>The Prime Minister has announced a Repeal Bill to convert EU law into domestic British law. This provides certainty for consumers, workers and businesses by maintaining existing laws wherever practicable.</p>","Suffolk Coastal","Dr Thérèse Coffey",,"2016-11-25T13:22:36.39Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641242/answer","Biography information for Dr Thérèse  Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641242/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641242/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2016-11-21","Environment Protection: EU Law","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what plans her Department has to retain the effect of EU environmental directives in UK law after the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Julie Elliott","Sunderland Central","Julie Elliott","54006"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641243","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2016-11-25","<p>The UK Recycling rate has increased from 11% at the turn of the century to 44.9% now. This increase is thanks in large part to the hard work of local authorities and householders to recycle more.</p><p> </p><p>The Government is committed to meeting the EU target to increase the preparing for reuse or recycling of wastes from households to 50% by 2020 and we regularly review progress to achieving this.</p><p> </p><p>Local authorities are best placed to determine the most appropriate waste collection and recycling services in their area and we work closely with them and the Waste and Recycling Action Programme (WRAP) to promote best practice and to increase the quantity and quality of material collected for recycling.</p>","Suffolk Coastal","Dr Thérèse Coffey",,"2016-11-25T13:16:15.223Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641243/answer","Biography information for Dr Thérèse  Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641243/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641243/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2016-11-21","Recycling","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what steps she plans to take to ensure that the UK meets the EU target to reuse and recycle 50 per cent of household waste by 2020.","false","Biography information for Julie Elliott","Sunderland Central","Julie Elliott","54005"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641244","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2016-11-24","<p>The Environment Agency has taken enforcement action against Rowanoak Waste Services Limited following poor compliance, including the exceedance of their legal waste quantities. On 29 April 2016 their environmental permit was revoked, preventing them from moving more waste to the site.</p><p>The revocation notice also required the removal of all waste on the site by 16 September 2016. Rowanoak Waste Services Limited failed to comply with this and the Environment Agency is now preparing to take further action against the company for non-compliance.</p><p>The Environment Agency always looks to take prosecution action against an operator who is found to have committed a criminal offence and will always seek to ensure that it remediates any environmental impact caused by its illegal activity.</p><p>The Environment Agency is working with the landowner, Dudley Borough Council and the West Midlands Fire and Rescue Service to minimise pollution and fire risk at the site and to have it cleared as soon as possible.</p><p> </p>","Suffolk Coastal","Dr Thérèse Coffey","54013 ; 54014","2016-11-24T15:35:55.64Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641244/answer","Biography information for Dr Thérèse  Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641244/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641244/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2016-11-21","Waste Disposal: Dudley","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what discussions her Department has had with the Environment Agency on removal of the mound of rubbish at the site operated by Rowan Oak Waste on Shaw Road, Dudley.","false","Biography information for Ian Austin","Dudley North","Ian Austin","54012"
