"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641247","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2016-11-24","<p>Following the extreme flood events of the winters of 2013/14 and 2015/16, HM Treasury provided the following exceptional additional funding to meet costs of responding to the flooding; and repairing, restoring and maintaining critical flood defences:</p><p> </p><p>2013/14 - £30m</p><p>2014/15 - £180m</p><p>2015/16 - £85m</p><p> </p>","Suffolk Coastal","Dr Thérèse Coffey",,"2016-11-24T16:58:02.183Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641247/answer","Biography information for Dr Thérèse  Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641247/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641247/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2016-11-21","Floods: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, pursuant to  the Answer of 17 November 2016 to Question 52825, what estimate she has made of the level of funding support received from HM Treasury for response and recovery activities relating to emergency events in each of the last five years; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","54010"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641248","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-11-30","<p>We are strengthening our European network of posts including by increasing the number of UK based staff posted, upgrading the seniority of a number of Heads of Mission jobs and increasing our representation in Geneva. We will continue to review staffing in the wider network as appropriate.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan",,"2016-11-30T16:57:29.08Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641248/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641248/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641248/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-11-21","EU Countries: Diplomatic Service","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what plans his Department has to increase its overseas diplomatic representation after the vote to leave the EU; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","53941"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641249","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-11-24","<p>The information available to the UK Government on Syria originates from a variety of intelligence and other sources, which it would not be appropriate to publish. The UK will, however, with our US and EU allies, continue to seek means of highlighting the responsibilities of the Syrian Regime and Russia for the humanitarian crisis in Syria and on seeking means to resolve it, including through maintaining EU resolve on sanctions.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2016-11-24T16:12:46.857Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641249/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641249/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641249/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-11-21","Syria: Military Intervention","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, if he will publish on a weekly basis information on Russian and Syrian air assets engaged in attacking civilian targets in Syria; if he will publish the identity of the officer in the chain of command under which those air assets operate; and if he will make such information available to his EU counterparts with responsibility for sanctions policy.","false","Biography information for Mr Andrew Mitchell","Sutton Coldfield","Mr Andrew Mitchell","54038"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641250","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-11-28","<p>We continually make clear to both the government of South Sudan and the Opposition that disrupting the efforts of humanitarian agencies to provide food for civilians in desperate need of assistance is absolutely unacceptable. In particular, the government must fulfil its commitment to improve access for humanitarian personnel to those who need our support. The Foreign and Commonwealth Office’s Africa Director raised this issue with the First Vice President on 23 November. We also raise humanitarian issues alongside other donors with representatives of the Government in the context of discussions about the peace process, organised by the Joint Monitoring and Evaluation Committee in Juba, most recently on 22 November.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2016-11-28T15:52:19.43Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641250/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641250/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641250/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-11-21","South Sudan: Food","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what representations he has made to his counterpart in South Sudan on stopping armed forces destroying food reserves and restricting access to food for civilians in that country.","false","Biography information for Imran Hussain","Bradford East","Imran Hussain","54048"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641251","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-11-28","<p>Non-governmental organisations (NGOs) are playing a vital part in providing lifesaving humanitarian support in South Sudan. The Department for International Development Director for East Africa met with the Minister for Humanitarian Affairs on 22 October to discuss the South Sudanese NGO Bill and to ensure that its implementation was not hindering NGOs in providing vital services. We are watching this situation closely, and are in dialogue with NGO forums and the partners that we fund directly.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2016-11-28T15:55:16.667Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641251/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641251/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641251/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-11-21","South Sudan: Migrant Workers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what discussions he has had with his counterpart in South Sudan on that country's restriction of employment of non-South Sudanese nationals by non-governmental organisations and other organisations.","false","Biography information for Imran Hussain","Bradford East","Imran Hussain","54060"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641252","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-11-28","<p>The mandate for the UN Mission in South Sudan (UNMISS) was extended for four months on 12 August, following extensive discussions in the UN Security Council. The effectiveness of the mission is reviewed monthly by Security Council members during consultations, which involve extensive discussions with all other members of the Council, and the mandate is due for renewal on 15 December. The UK Permanent Representative to the UN represents the UK Government during these discussions.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2016-11-28T15:39:46.757Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641252/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641252/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641252/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-11-21","UN Mission in South Sudan","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what representations he or the UK representative to the UN have made to other UN Security Council member states on the extension of the UN mission in South Sudan.","false","Biography information for Imran Hussain","Bradford East","Imran Hussain","54062"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641253","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-11-28","<p>We regularly discuss South Sudan with senior African Union Commission (AUC) officials in Addis Ababa and Juba and raise it regularly with individual African Union Member States on a bilateral basis, including at the Joint Monitoring and Evaluation Commission Partners meeting in Kampala on 10 November. Most recently, our Ambassador to South Sudan met with the AU Special Representative for South Sudan in Juba on 20 November, while our Ambassador to Ethiopia and UK Permanent Representative to the African Union met the AUC Commissioner for Peace and Security on 21 October and raised South Sudan with him then.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2016-11-28T15:37:40.147Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641253/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641253/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641253/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-11-21","South Sudan: Armed Conflict","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what discussions he has had on the situation in South Sudan with member states of the African Union and representatives from the African Union.","false","Biography information for Imran Hussain","Bradford East","Imran Hussain","54061"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641254","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-11-29","<p>I discussed Taiwan with Assistant Minister Liu Haixing on 15 August 2016 during my visit to Beijing. British and Chinese officials also regularly exchange views on this topic. We reiterate that the UK’s position on Taiwan remains unchanged and that issues should be settled by the people on both sides of the Strait.</p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"2016-11-29T17:31:54.38Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641254/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641254/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641254/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-11-21","China: Taiwan","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what discussions he has had with his Chinese counterpart on that country's relationship with Taiwan.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","54088"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641255","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-11-29","<p>The focus of discussions between the UK and China on North Korea is how we both use our relations to dissuade Pyongyang from pursuing nuclear weapons. I discussed this objective with Assistant Foreign Minister Liu Haixing on 15 August 2016 during my visit to Beijing, and I raised it most recently with the Chinese Ambassador on 27 October 2016.</p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"2016-11-29T17:33:04.533Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641255/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641255/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641255/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-11-21","North Korea: Foreign Relations","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what discussions he has had with his Chinese counterpart on steps to improve relations between North Korea and the UK.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","54089"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641256","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-11-24","<p>​The UK regularly raises human rights cases with the Iranian government including the continued persecution of religious minorities. We are aware of restrictions on translating Christian texts in Iran. We condemn these restrictions alongside reports of Christian property being seized and reports of theological schools being closed. We call on Iran to cease harassment of all religious minorities and to fulfil its international and domestic obligations to allow freedom of religion to all Iranians.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2016-11-24T15:36:49.447Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641256/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641256/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641256/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-11-21","Iran: Christianity","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, if he will raise the case of the seizure of the retreat centre in Mohammadshahr in Karaj belonging to the Council of Assemblies of God Churches with his Iranian counterparts.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","54091"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641257","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-11-24","<p>​The UK regularly raises human rights cases with the Iranian government including the continued persecution of religious minorities. We are aware of restrictions on translating Christian texts in Iran. We condemn these restrictions alongside reports of Christian property being seized and reports of theological schools being closed. We call on Iran to cease harassment of all religious minorities and to fulfil its international and domestic obligations to allow freedom of religion to all Iranians.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2016-11-24T15:34:07.65Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641257/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641257/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641257/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-11-21","Iran: Christianity","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, whether he has received representations on the banning of the publication of bibles and Christian literature in Farsi.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","54092"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641258","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-11-24","<p>​The UK regularly raises human rights cases with the Iranian government including the continued persecution of religious minorities. We are aware of restrictions on translating Christian texts in Iran. We condemn these restrictions alongside reports of Christian property being seized and reports of theological schools being closed. We call on Iran to cease harassment of all religious minorities and to fulfil its international and domestic obligations to allow freedom of religion to all Iranians.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2016-11-24T15:38:36.82Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641258/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641258/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641258/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-11-21","Iran: Christianity","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what reports his Department has received on the closure of (a) church-owned theological schools and (b) leadership development programmes in Iran.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","54093"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641259","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-11-28","<p>​Our Embassy in Tel Aviv has raised, and continues to raise, the detention of Mr Sharary with the Israeli authorities, most recently on 15 November. Consular officials continue to provide consular support to Mr Sharary and his family.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2016-11-28T15:41:17.49Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641259/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641259/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641259/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-11-21","Faiz Mahmoud Ahmed Sherari","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, whether Faiz Mahmoud Ahmed Sherari was provided with consular assistance from the British Government during his recent detention in Israel.","false","Biography information for Daniel Zeichner","Cambridge","Daniel Zeichner","53884"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641260","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-11-28","<p>​Our Embassy in Tel Aviv has raised, and continues to raise, the detention of Mr Sharary with the Israeli authorities, most recently on 15 November. Consular officials continue to provide consular support to Mr Sharary and his family.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2016-11-28T15:43:05.65Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641260/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641260/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641260/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-11-21","Faiz Mahmoud Ahmed Sherari","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what representations he has made to the Israeli government on the recent detention of British citizen Faiz Mahmoud Ahmed Sherari.","false","Biography information for Daniel Zeichner","Cambridge","Daniel Zeichner","53885"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641261","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-11-24","<p>The status of Yau-Wai-ching and Sixtus Leung is for the Hong Kong' Courts to decide. This issue is still the subject of legal proceedings in Hong Kong. The Joint Declaration and the Basic Law underpin the implementation of 'One Country, Two Systems' and remain the foundations for the high degree of autonomy of Hong Kong and the rights and freedoms of its people.</p><p> </p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"2016-11-24T17:17:59.257Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641261/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641261/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641261/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-11-21","Hong Kong Legislative Council: Membership","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, if he will make an assessment of the effect of the banning of Yau Wai-ching and Baggio Sixtus Leung from taking office in the Hong Kong Legislative Council by the Chinese government on the Sino-British Joint Declaration; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","59324"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641262","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-11-24","<p>Following recent reports about Mrs Zaghari-Ratcliffe’s health we are urgently seeking information from the Iranian authorities to raise our concerns. Mrs Zaghari-Ratcliffe’s case remains a top priority and our Ambassador in Tehran and Embassy officials are in regular contact with the Iranians on this matter. We shall continue to lobby them at the highest level at every opportunity.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2016-11-24T15:23:00.287Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641262/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641262/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641262/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-11-21","Nazanin Zaghari-Ratcliffe","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent reports he has received on the health of Nazanin Zaghari-Ratcliffe.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","53901"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641263","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-11-24","<p>​I have asked our Ambassador in Tehran to urgently raise our concerns about reports of Nazanin Zaghari-Ratcliffe’s deteriorating health with the Iranian authorities, and to request she has appropriate access to medical treatment. Our Ambassador regularly raises Mrs Zaghari-Ratcliffe’s case with the Iranians including President Rouhani and Foreign Minister Zarif. The Foreign Secretary, my Rt Hon. Friend the Member for Uxbridge and South Ruislip (Mr Johnson), most recently wrote to his Iranian counterpart on 4 November to raise our concerns on all our consular cases.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2016-11-24T15:15:47.877Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641263/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641263/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641263/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-11-21","Nazanin Zaghari-Ratcliffe","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, whether he plans to (a) write to and (b) meet his Iranian counterpart to discuss the case of Nazanin Zaghari-Ratcliffe following reports of her deteriorating health.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","53899"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641264","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-11-24","<p>​Since we were made aware of the arrest of Mrs Nazanin Zaghari-Ratcliffe Ministers and officials have raised the case repeatedly, at all levels, with the Iranian government. Most recently, The Prime Minister, my Rt Hon. Friend the Member for Maidenhead (Mrs May), and The Foreign Secretary, my Rt Hon. Friend the Member for Uxbridge and South Ruislip (Mr Johnson), raised Mrs Zaghari- Ratcliffe’s case with their Iranian counterparts during the UN General Assembly in September. The Prime Minister followed up her concerns in writing to President Rouhani on 3 October. We will continue to raise these cases with the Iranian Government at every available opportunity.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2016-11-24T15:18:31.583Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641264/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641264/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641264/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-11-21","Nazanin Zaghari-Ratcliffe","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent representations he has made to his Iranian counterpart on the case of Nazanin Zaghari-Ratcliffe.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","53900"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641265","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-11-25","<p>​We encourage Emirati authorities to follow due process in criminal proceedings and ensure the human rights of all Emirati citizens are respected. We believe freedom of expression is a universal human right and that people must be allowed to freely discuss and debate issues, challenge their governments and make informed decisions in accordance with international human rights law. Where we have concerns we make these clear to Emirati authorities, as part of our broader strategic engagement.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2016-11-25T12:38:27.913Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641265/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641265/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641265/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-11-21","United Arab Emirates: Freedom of Expression","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what steps his Department is taking to support people in the United Arab Emirates who are threatened, harassed or face arrest for exercising their right of freedom of expression.","false","Biography information for Rebecca Long Bailey","Salford and Eccles","Rebecca Long Bailey","53871"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641266","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-11-25","<p>The British Government followed the trial of Mr Al Roken closely. While we welcomed the fact that local media and relatives of the 94 were allowed to attend the trial, we raised concerns about some aspects of the way the trial was conducted, such as lack of access to international observers, an accusation that defendants could not access their lawyers and the length of the sentencing.</p><p>The then Foreign Secretary, my Rt Hon. Friend The Lord Hague of Richmond, and the former Minister for the Middle East, my Rt Hon. Friend the Member for North East Bedfordshire (Mr Burt) raised the importance of due process in criminal proceedings, upholding international standards of justice and ensuring the human rights of all Emirati citizens are fully respected, including the rights of freedom of expression and association.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2016-11-25T12:40:51.267Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641266/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641266/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641266/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-11-21","United Arab Emirates: Human Rights","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what steps he has taken to support the release of Dr Mohamed al-Roken and other human right activists imprisoned in the United Arab Emirates in 2013.","false","Biography information for Rebecca Long Bailey","Salford and Eccles","Rebecca Long Bailey","53872"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641267","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-11-25","<p>​We believe freedom of expression is a universal human right and that people must be allowed to freely discuss and debate issues, challenge their governments and make informed decisions. Where we have concerns we make these clear to Emirati authorities, as part of our broader strategic engagement.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2016-11-25T12:43:09.927Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641267/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641267/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641267/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-11-21","United Arab Emirates: Freedom of Expression","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what discussions he has had with his United Arab Emirates counterpart on the respect for freedom of expression in that country.","false","Biography information for Rebecca Long Bailey","Salford and Eccles","Rebecca Long Bailey","53873"
