"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641269","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2016-11-25","<p>Government remains committed to reconsidering the case for ratification of the 2001 Convention on the Protection of Underwater Cultural Heritage. A decision on timescales for reviewing the Convention will be made in late Spring 2017.</p>","Chatham and Aylesford","Tracey Crouch",,"2016-11-25T07:50:04.207Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641269/answer","Biography information for Tracey Crouch","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641269/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641269/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2016-11-21","Convention on the Protection of the Underwater Cultural Heritage","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what plans the Government has to ratify the UNESCO Convention on the Protection of Underwater Cultural Heritage; what discussions she has had with Cabinet colleagues on that ratification; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Sir Jeffrey M. Donaldson","Lagan Valley","Sir Jeffrey M. Donaldson","53922"
