"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641326","Department for International Development","false","2016-11-24","<p>The UK has monitored the situation since heavy persistent rain started falling in parts of the Dominican Republic on 7 November and stood ready to offer assistance if required.</p><p>The Government of the Dominican Republic have not requested international assistance.</p>","Stockton South","James Wharton",,"2016-11-24T16:30:47.6Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641326/answer","Biography information for James Wharton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641326/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641326/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2016-11-21","Dominican Republic: Floods","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what support her Department is providing to the Dominican Republic to assist with the flooding in that country.","false","Biography information for Will Quince","Colchester","Will Quince","53910"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641327","Department for International Development","false","2016-11-29","<p>The Secretary of State recently returned from Sierra Leone and saw first-hand that although the Ebola crisis has ended, the country faces major development challenges, including some of the worst child and infant mortality rates in the world.</p><p>Ebola has made these challenges worse and reversed, for example, much of the progress in health made since the civil war, with high numbers of health staff dying and sharp falls in essential services, such as treatment of malaria and immunisation. UK support is helping the Government of Sierra Leone to build up better health services and save lives, ensure children get a better education, increase access to water and sanitation, and lay the groundwork for increased economic development.</p><p>Our cross-government response to the 2014/15 Ebola crisis saved lives and stopped the outbreak decimating development in Sierra Leone. Halting the disease in West Africa was the single most important way of preventing Ebola from infecting people in the UK.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Stockton South","James Wharton",,"2016-11-29T16:43:36.07Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641327/answer","Biography information for James Wharton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641327/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641327/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2016-11-21","Sierra Leone: Politics and Government","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what recent assessment she has made of the humanitarian situation in Sierra Leone.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","53883"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641328","Department for International Development","false","2016-11-28","<p>The UN Commission on the Status of Women (UNCSW) provides an important opportunity to advance better outcomes for girls and women.</p><p>The government will ensure high level representation at the next UNCSW in March 2017.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2016-11-28T17:13:45.187Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641328/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641328/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641328/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2016-11-21","UN Commission on the Status of Women","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, if she will attend the sixty-first session of the UN Commission on the Status of Women in New York in March 2017.","false","Biography information for Patrick Grady","Glasgow North","Patrick Grady","53867"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641329","Department for International Development","false","2016-11-28","<p>The UK Government has a strong domestic and international record on promoting gender equality. Although not working specifically under the auspices of UN Women’s Step it Up for Gender Equality initiative, the UK Cabinet is firmly committed to this agenda.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2016-11-28T17:15:31.67Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641329/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641329/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641329/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2016-11-21","Developing Countries: Females","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what discussions she has had with Cabinet colleagues on promoting a cross-government approach to implementing the UN's Step it Up for Gender Equality initiative.","false","Biography information for Patrick Grady","Glasgow North","Patrick Grady","53869"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641330","Department for International Development","false","2016-11-28","<p>The Secretary of State met the Executive Director of UN Women during the UN General Assembly in September, and would expect to meet her again in the course of regular business.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2016-11-28T17:14:33.827Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641330/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641330/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641330/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2016-11-21","UN Women","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, whether she plans to meet the Executive Director of UN Women.","false","Biography information for Patrick Grady","Glasgow North","Patrick Grady","53858"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641331","Department for International Development","false","2016-11-25","<p>As set out in the UN’s Global Goals, urgent action is needed to mobilise, redirect and unlock the transformative power of trillions of dollars of private resources to deliver on sustainable development objectives. Long-term investments, including foreign direct investment, are needed in critical sectors, especially in developing countries. CDC’s work is focused on mobilising capital for specific sustainable development priorities such as health, education and infrastructure, helping to fill the annual financing gap of $2.5 trillion needed every year and deliver against the Goals by 2030.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2016-11-25T16:19:42.713Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641331/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641331/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641331/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2016-11-21","CDC: Investment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, with reference to paragraph 10 of the explanatory memorandum to the Commonwealth Development Corporation Bill, what estimate she has made of market demand over Commonwealth Development Corporation's next strategy cycle.","false","Biography information for Stephen Doughty","Cardiff South and Penarth","Stephen Doughty","54037"
