"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641333","Department for International Development","false","2016-11-28","<p>Due to the severity and protracted nature of the food security crisis in South Sudan, DFID has signed multi-year agreements with the World Food Programme and the International Committee of the Red Cross. This is a cost-effective way of providing emergency food assistance which allows us to reach more people. This year, UK funds have supported between 1.3 and 1.9 million people per month. The UK will continue to be vocal in lobbying the Government of South Sudan and others on facilitating humanitarian access for aid agencies.</p>","Stockton South","James Wharton",,"2016-11-28T16:24:06.233Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641333/answer","Biography information for James Wharton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641333/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641333/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2016-11-21","South Sudan: Food","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what support her Department is providing to help to support food-insecure people in South Sudan.","false","Biography information for Imran Hussain","Bradford East","Imran Hussain","54050"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641334","Department for International Development","false","2016-11-28","<p>The UK is the second largest bilateral donor to the humanitarian response in South Sudan. We expect to provide assistance to 3 million people between 2015 and 2020, the majority of whom are internally displaced people, but also those living in the host communities supporting them. Our support will include life-saving food and clean drinking water as well as sanitation, shelter and health care.</p>","Stockton South","James Wharton",,"2016-11-28T16:17:17.64Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641334/answer","Biography information for James Wharton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641334/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641334/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2016-11-21","South Sudan: Internally Displaced People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what support her Department is providing to help support internally displaced South Sudanese refugees.","false","Biography information for Imran Hussain","Bradford East","Imran Hussain","54051"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641335","Department for International Development","false","2016-11-28","<p>DFID is the lead donor to the multi-donor Health Pooled Fund (HPF) in South Sudan which provides primary health services through over 1,000 health facilities in eight of the 10 states in South Sudan. The HPF has supported the cholera outbreak response through the provision of essential medicines, supplies and by setting up cholera treatment centres in the affected states.</p>","Stockton South","James Wharton",,"2016-11-28T16:19:17.11Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641335/answer","Biography information for James Wharton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641335/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/641335/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2016-11-21","South Sudan: Cholera","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what support her Department is providing to help combat cholera outbreaks in South Sudan.","false","Biography information for Imran Hussain","Bradford East","Imran Hussain","54049"
